						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 5) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 10th century.</p>						

						<p>This record registers the death of Bīra-Baḷoja, when Bīra Baḷanjinga Vemma[ra*]sa son of Siṅghapuli captured 300 bulls. It states that Vajjaradēva was ruling the country during the period.</p>						

						</summary>
